Version: 0.1.27
Date: 2026-04-18

Changes:
- Runtime cleanup and simplification:
  - extract shared workspace-change analysis helpers so runner/query-engine
    stop carrying duplicate git/path logic.
  - replace the lightweight task-registry wrapper with direct local-turn and
    verification-round entrypoints.
  - move loop guardrail and convergence helpers out of the main runtime loop
    so the core loop is easier to read without changing behavior.
- Tooling and prompt guidance:
  - add model guidance support for high-signal builtin tool descriptions.
  - tighten several builtin tool metadata/details and related tests.
- Project positioning and docs:
  - rewrite the README around Merlion as a lightweight reference
    implementation rather than a feature-list product pitch.
  - add a linked Simplified Chinese README.
- Bench and validation:
  - add SWE-bench Lite bench script wiring and extra benchmark coverage.

Validation:
- npm run typecheck
- npm test

Related commits:
- refactor(runtime): simplify task entrypoints and shared workspace analysis
- refactor(runtime): split loop guardrails from main agent loop
- docs(readme): reposition merlion as a lightweight reference implementation
